    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1937-09-02T07:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1937-09-02T07:00:00-05:00" n="321"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d321">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">211.68/156: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Chargé in Greece</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Shantz</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Athens</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1937-09-02T14:00:00+02:00"
                            >September 2, 1937—2 p.m.</date>
                        <lb/>[Received September 2—9:45 a.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>63. Department’s telegram No. 34, August 9, 5 p.m. Protocol signed today.<note
                        n="21" xml:id="d321fn21">Printed as Department of State Executive Agreement
                        Series No. 114. Text identical with draft protocol, <ref target="#pg_428">p.
                            428</ref>. In despatch No. 2185, March 28, 1938, the Minister in Greece
                        reported that the Greek Government had ratified the interpretative protocol
                        by Emergency Law No. 1115 of February 26, 1938, making it legally effective
                        as of the date of its signature (211.68/167).</note>
                </p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Shantz</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
